tter. If you don't have a favorite movie adaptation, do you have a favorite movie ?  It's a Netflix series which is based on books set in the 1800's. It's very English! But if you like period dramas, you might enjoy it! Thanks for the suggestion, I will add it to list. Do you want Netflix often ?",test_622_4
"I am a stay-at-home mom of three kids. I am getting a teaching degree. I have travelled to many places. I'm single. I would like to travel. I am married. My parents were in the military. I go to open mic nights. My hobby is illustrating children's books. I run long-distance. I run in the mornings. I like the color turquoise. I like blues colors, such as turquoise and teal.","Hi, how are you? I'm a stay-at-home mom of 3 getting my degree in teaching. Wow! I'm single, love to travel...i've been all over the world. I'm happily married but would love to travel when my kids are grown! I'm an army brat. My parents met in high school. Yes. For fun, I love to go to open mic nights. Sounds interesting! I'm a children's book illustrator. That's my main hobby. Great! I'm a long distance runner. Great for the heart. I run some mornings too. Clears the mind. Yes, it does. What's your favorite color? I love turquoise. Same! Teal, turqouise. I like most blues. So do I! Sounds like we have lots in common.",test_624_1
I am not talented enough to perform at open mics. I watch open mic shows. I have fun at open mics. I like comedy. I have children. I have a husband. I visited Africa a couple of years ago. I lived in Germany and the Phillipines when I was a kid. I went on a safari in Africa. I wish I could have fun on a trip someday. I got close to a pride of lions. I was a little nervous on the safari bus being so close to the animals.,"I just go to watch. I don't really have any talent to get up and perform myself. I go to several, but I prefer going to the comedy club.  I like watching comedy.  You should go sometime with your husband. It's a lot of fun! Maybe one day If I can get someone to look after our kids. Which country have you travel to? Well, as a kid my parents were stationed in Germany, and in the Phillipines.  I took a trip to africa a couple of years ago though.   Africa was great. you'd think it would be sad to see the way some of the villagers live, but they were all so joyful and welcoming.  I traveled all throughout central Africa.  Even went on a safari! Well, I got to see a pride of lions up close...maybe a little too close!  But it was beautiful.  unlike anything you can see here. Well, we were on the safari bus, and the guides instilled a lot of confidence. They weren't afraid, so it must not have been as dangerous as it seemed.  My heart skipped a few beats though!",test_624_2
"I went on vacation to Africa. I like adventure and things with historical value. I would like to visit Rome and Germany. I would like to visit Italy. I used to live around Frankfurt, Germany.","After hearing about your trip to Africa, I decided to finally book a fun vacation of my own. Where do you think I should go? Well what sort of things do you like to do? Do you like hot weather, trying new food or cities? I dont prefer hot weather at all!  I like adventure and things with historical value. Ah ok, well Europe has a lot of history, especially places like Italy and Greece. You can visit during the cooler months so it is not so hot. Yes that sounds like a good plan.  I would love to see some of the sites in Rome and Germany as well.  What area of Germany did you live in? I would love to visit the old Roman parts of Italy. I lived around Frankfurt, it has some wonderful architecture.   I always went them. the atmosphere was wonderful and the food was even better. Have you ever tried German sausages? You can just eat them as they are in a roll. They are enormous so I am normally happy to eating a sausage on its own while I walk around the market.",test_624_3
